metadata.name: Stuck Inside #58
metadata.description:
As Spring transitions to Summer, flowers are in full bloom. With no outside view from my desk, I find myself daydreaming of walks around the yard, watering flowers, and watching the insects.

This is a simple and abstract kinetic piece that represents the daydreams I have while working, as I look forward to my next break, when I can walk outside for a few minutes.

100% of secondary sale royalties will go to the Processing Foundation.

The piece is responsive and will adapt to your browser window size. Press SPACE to export a high-resolution PNG image of the current frame at the current aspect ratio. 

If you are using Safari, the animation will be rate limited until you click or tap once on the piece.

metadata.name: Deconstructions #252
metadata.description:
Deconstructions is a further experiment with blending 3 colors and 3 different textures to create structural/abstract compositions. It's a search for beauty within asymmetrical/unsynchronized forms and disharmonic structures.


Probabilities;

- 18 compositions with variations.

- 2 background colors.

- 3 different particle starting placements.

- 21 different base color palettes. (1 monochrome) 

- 2 different alpha types; tangential & randomized.

- Different edges.

- Several starting positions and styles (wavy or straight).

Additional animation features with different shapes, angles, direction and style.


In live mode, press â€˜sâ€™ to save as .png (1500x2000 px)

It can take up to a minute to render or longer in low-performance computers. Enjoy the process!


Made with p5.js

metadata.name: Ridge Scribbles #25
metadata.description:
Ridge scribbles is the first piece of a small series around mountain landscapes using different rendering techniques.

A heightmap is generated using fractal noise with different parameters and scales. Then we generate tens of thousands of paths by using a gradient descent algorithm with momentum, starting at random positions on the reversed heightmap. Those paths are then rendered using one of 11 different colour palettes.

Press "s" to save a screenshot.

Original artwork by William Watkins Â· Lyon, 2022

metadata.name: fx_dungeon #86
metadata.description:
Welcome to the fx_dungeon. Every cartridge comes loaded with a random amount of levels between 2 (common) and 7 (rare). Your goal is to collect all the coins that are disseminated around the level. Each cartridge comes with the total amount of coins that can be collected displayed on the front. 

Token levels are generated from the transaction hash and are never the same between different tokens. Scattered around the levels are also some random amount of decorative props. There are different types of props, and I added those to the features as well.

Finally, each cartridge comes in different conditions. You could get one in perfect conditions, or one that's been used over and over. Don't worry, each cartridge has been tested and it's working properly anyways!!

This is just a simple game I made learning how to code for creative projects. It's also rumored that's a Golden Edition of this cartridge can be obtained somehow..

## Controls
- Move the player around using WASD or the arrow keys. Interact with stairs using SPACEBAR or E
- You can click the image to toggle sound on or off

## Credits
- I'm using p5js and I also tweaked to my needs a tutorial from Daniel Schiffman about raycasting
- The ambient music is from Joshua McLean, it's called Mountain Trials (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=L_OYo2RS8iU&list=PLwJjxqYuirCLkq42mGw4XKGQlpZSfxsYd&index=8) and it's released under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International license
